1
00:00:14,767 --> 00:00:15,633
You're just a boyfriend.
I'm her mother.

2
00:00:16,767 --> 00:00:17,633
Come on, Yenyen.

3
00:00:17,767 --> 00:00:18,700
Mom, I'm not coming with you.

4
00:00:18,833 --> 00:00:20,033
Don't be so stubborn!

5
00:00:20,167 --> 00:00:22,333
Do you want to be with these
evil people?

6
00:00:22,467 --> 00:00:24,000
Why, Mom? Are you a good person?

7
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:25,667
Don't I matter to you anymore?

8
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:28,500
I can't forget every good thing
she did for me

9
00:00:28,633 --> 00:00:30,533
when you abandoned me.

10
00:00:30,667 --> 00:00:35,267
She may be unpleasant to others,
but she's a good mother.

11
00:00:35,433 --> 00:00:38,100
And a good wife.

12
00:00:38,233 --> 00:00:42,867
She might file a kidnapping case
against us just to get revenge.

13
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:45,100
But I stayed with Red
of my own will.

14
00:00:45,233 --> 00:00:47,300
But we still have no right
to her.

15
00:00:47,433 --> 00:00:50,333
Unless, of course,
you two get married.

16
00:00:50,467 --> 00:00:53,833
But up until that time, Amanda
is still your guardian.

17
00:00:53,967 --> 00:00:55,900
Because she's your mother.

18
00:00:56,033 --> 00:00:57,200
She was right.

19
00:00:57,333 --> 00:01:00,900
She has more right to you
because she's your mother.

20
00:01:01,033 --> 00:01:02,700
We love each other,

21
00:01:02,833 --> 00:01:05,267
and that gives us the right
to each other.

22
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:07,833
Yen, I think this
is the right time.

23
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:09,333
Let's get married.

24
00:01:09,467 --> 00:01:11,367
So they can't separate us again.

25
00:01:11,500 --> 00:01:14,400
I'm on top right now.

26
00:01:14,533 --> 00:01:17,667
Did you come here to rub
that in?

27
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:19,367
This is your karma.

28
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:22,633
And I'll make sure you'll
not only rot in jail.

29
00:01:22,767 --> 00:01:25,400
You'll die here too.

30
00:01:25,533 --> 00:01:28,467
Well, be ready once I get out.

31
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:31,633
Because I'll come for you.

32
00:01:31,767 --> 00:01:33,333
I'll wait for you.

33
00:01:33,467 --> 00:01:36,567
I'll forgive you for Red's sake.

34
00:01:36,700 --> 00:01:41,067
What matters is you didn't
abandon me.

35
00:01:41,233 --> 00:01:42,900
Our lawyer has posted
bail already.

36
00:01:43,033 --> 00:01:44,833
He's just processing
your papers.

37
00:01:44,967 --> 00:01:46,533
Do you know how much
it stinks here?

38
00:01:46,667 --> 00:01:49,267
Even the people in that jail
smell.

39
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:51,267
Rina went out of jail already.
She posted bail.

40
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:53,333
We were informed that
she could post bail.

41
00:01:53,467 --> 00:01:54,467
What do you want us to do?

42
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,033
I want Rina to get beaten up.

43
00:01:56,167 --> 00:01:57,400
So, you think we're stinky?

44
00:01:59,933 --> 00:02:02,400
Now tell us we stink!

45
00:02:02,533 --> 00:02:04,167
Don't ever tell anyone.

46
00:02:04,300 --> 00:02:07,300
Or else I'll kill you.

47
00:02:48,167 --> 00:02:49,300
Sit down.

48
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:04,800
Did you like my gift?

49
00:03:04,933 --> 00:03:06,833
I heard you're getting out
of jail.

50
00:03:06,967 --> 00:03:10,900
That's why I gave you
a surprise.

51
00:03:11,033 --> 00:03:15,900
You're a monster, Amanda.

52
00:03:16,033 --> 00:03:18,400
Your surprise is nothing.

53
00:03:18,533 --> 00:03:21,933
It's just physical pain.

54
00:03:22,100 --> 00:03:23,967
But you...

55
00:03:24,100 --> 00:03:30,567
brace yourself because
you will surely get hurt.

56
00:03:30,700 --> 00:03:32,600
Oh, really?

57
00:03:35,133 --> 00:03:38,833
Didn't you make me get used
to the pain?

58
00:03:38,967 --> 00:03:42,233
So, your words don't affect me
anymore.

59
00:03:42,367 --> 00:03:43,833
I won't be bothered by it.

60
00:03:46,467 --> 00:03:49,233
You might kill yourself
when you hear about it.

61
00:03:49,367 --> 00:03:50,733
Come again?

62
00:03:50,867 --> 00:03:55,667
You might kill yourself
when you hear about it.

63
00:03:56,767 --> 00:03:58,933
What are you bluffing about?

64
00:03:59,067 --> 00:04:01,500
You can't fool me anymore.

65
00:04:01,633 --> 00:04:04,100
Oh, is that so?

66
00:04:04,233 --> 00:04:09,433
What if I tell you
that Red and Eden

67
00:04:09,567 --> 00:04:12,033
are already getting married?

68
00:04:12,167 --> 00:04:15,267
Oh, did you get surprised?

69
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:16,767
You weren't aware, were you?

70
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:20,733
Well, you're not invited anyway.

71
00:04:41,733 --> 00:04:42,800
Excuse me.

72
00:04:42,933 --> 00:04:44,400
Thank you.

73
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:48,633
Gosh, Eden!

74
00:04:48,767 --> 00:04:50,900
Why did you put your wedding
dress on?

75
00:04:51,033 --> 00:04:52,067
That's the reason we came here.

76
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:54,600
To fit the gown, remember?

77
00:04:54,733 --> 00:04:57,067
I thought you were just going
to check it.

78
00:04:57,200 --> 00:05:01,833
Eden, the elderlies believe
that wearing your wedding dress

79
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:05,367
before the wedding
brings bad luck.

80
00:05:05,500 --> 00:05:07,800
Are we elders?

81
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:10,233
It's their belief. Not ours.

82
00:05:10,367 --> 00:05:12,467
It's okay to try your wedding
gown nowadays.

83
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:18,800
To make sure it will
perfectly fit me.

84
00:05:18,933 --> 00:05:20,533
Well, you have a point.

85
00:05:20,667 --> 00:05:24,900
I hope I can accomplish
my bridesmaid duties.

86
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:26,667
Red and I are getting married.

87
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:30,933
Nothing can stop us no matter
what happens.

88
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:41,333
Lucho, find out where Eden
and Red will get married!

89
00:05:41,467 --> 00:05:43,433
Relax. I'll take care of it.

90
00:05:43,567 --> 00:05:45,367
Amanda, leave Eden be.

91
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:48,100
She has her own life now.

92
00:05:48,233 --> 00:05:50,000
I won't let that happen!

93
00:05:50,133 --> 00:05:53,233
Once they're married, I can
never get my daughter back!

94
00:05:53,367 --> 00:05:54,767
You can't get your daughter back

95
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:56,867
even if they're not married
anyway.

96
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:58,533
You tried, didn't you?

97
00:05:58,667 --> 00:05:59,833
It's different this time.

98
00:05:59,967 --> 00:06:05,367
If I have to force her to come
with me, I will!

99
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:07,700
I won't wait for her to come
back of her own accord.

100
00:06:07,867 --> 00:06:10,567
They can't get married!

101
00:06:10,700 --> 00:06:12,600
They will make my daughter's
life miserable!

102
00:06:12,733 --> 00:06:14,733
Rina's just going to take
revenge on her!

103
00:06:14,867 --> 00:06:16,900
Eden's life will get ruined!

104
00:06:29,033 --> 00:06:30,700
How are you feeling?

105
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:33,000
Can you go to Red and Eden's
wedding?

106
00:06:34,367 --> 00:06:38,467
I can't miss their wedding.

107
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:41,233
This is a special day
for our son.

108
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:43,000
But you're not feeling well.

109
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:49,033
Victor.

110
00:06:49,167 --> 00:06:50,700
I'm fine, okay?

111
00:06:50,833 --> 00:06:52,500
I can do it.

112
00:06:52,633 --> 00:06:55,167
I don't feel any pain.

113
00:06:55,300 --> 00:07:00,600
Amanda will be in more pain.

114
00:07:00,733 --> 00:07:02,700
You're thinking
about Amanda again?

115
00:07:02,833 --> 00:07:06,967
She can't accept that the kids
are already getting married.

116
00:07:07,100 --> 00:07:09,567
She wants to take
her daughter back,

117
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:11,733
but Eden doesn't
want her anymore.

118
00:07:11,867 --> 00:07:13,467
This is a slap on her face.

119
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:16,833
That Eden and Red
are getting married.

120
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,867
The kids made the decision
to marry.

121
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:21,967
We didn't use them to get
revenge on Amanda.

122
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:32,067
You're right. But if I can use
this to hurt Amanda, why not?

123
00:07:33,633 --> 00:07:34,567
Let's go.

124
00:07:34,700 --> 00:07:35,833
The kids are waiting.

125
00:07:35,967 --> 00:07:37,200
Okay.

126
00:07:43,567 --> 00:07:47,400
The fight is still on, Amanda.

127
00:08:22,733 --> 00:08:27,667
Yenyen, take this ring...

128
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:30,367
as a sign of my love
and faithfulness to you.

129
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:39,667
I made this for you...

130
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:47,733
to remind us that we'll
stay together forever.

131
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:55,433
After everything that happened
to us on this island,

132
00:08:57,167 --> 00:08:59,133
I only feel one thing.

133
00:09:03,033 --> 00:09:09,067
The trees...

134
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:10,600
the plants...

135
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,300
the sea...

136
00:09:14,433 --> 00:09:17,700
and the rain are witnesses...

137
00:09:17,833 --> 00:09:26,400
I hope these sea shells will
bind us together...

138
00:09:28,533 --> 00:09:30,000
forever.

139
00:09:49,267 --> 00:09:50,767
Red...

140
00:09:50,900 --> 00:09:54,767
wear this ring as a sign
of my love and fidelity...

141
00:09:54,900 --> 00:09:56,800
forever and ever.

142
00:10:04,833 --> 00:10:06,633
- Who are you?
- Everyone, stay still.

143
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:12,700
I won't say congratulations
and best wishes

144
00:10:12,833 --> 00:10:14,333
because the wedding
won't happen.

145
00:10:14,467 --> 00:10:16,367
Mom, aren't you going
to leave us alone?

146
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:18,033
No.

147
00:10:18,167 --> 00:10:19,533
I'll get you.

148
00:10:19,667 --> 00:10:20,767
Don't touch her!

149
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:22,167
Let go of my daughter.

150
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:25,200
How often do I have to tell you
I'm not coming with you?

151
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:26,933
You don't know
what you're doing!

152
00:10:27,067 --> 00:10:28,900
No! You don't know
what you're doing!

153
00:10:29,033 --> 00:10:30,667
Your daughter doesn't
want you anymore!

154
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:31,733
Leave her alone!

155
00:10:31,867 --> 00:10:32,900
Amanda, please!

156
00:10:33,033 --> 00:10:33,900
Let the kids do what they want!

157
00:10:34,033 --> 00:10:37,100
I won't let my daughter
marry your son!

158
00:10:37,267 --> 00:10:38,700
You're not going to decide
for her!

159
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:40,167
She will make a choice!

160
00:10:40,300 --> 00:10:41,733
Who do you think you are?

161
00:10:41,867 --> 00:10:43,367
You are still just a boyfriend.

162
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:44,433
She's my daughter.

163
00:10:44,567 --> 00:10:45,467
Yen!

164
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:47,433
Don't hurt my son!

165
00:10:47,567 --> 00:10:49,033
Red, don't fight!

166
00:10:50,767 --> 00:10:54,367
You'll get more than that
if you don't stop.

167
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:55,933
Red, don't do anything.
I'll go with my mom.

168
00:10:56,067 --> 00:10:57,400
- Yes, you're coming with me.
- Yen, don't go with her.

169
00:10:57,533 --> 00:10:58,500
- Let's put an end to this.
- Don't leave me.

170
00:10:58,633 --> 00:10:59,467
Red, I don't want
you to get hurt.

171
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:01,600
Shut up! Stop!
Stop talking to that man.

172
00:11:01,733 --> 00:11:03,767
- You're delaying us.
- Red, let them be.

173
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:05,800
I'll get you back.
I'll come and get you.

174
00:11:05,933 --> 00:11:08,067
You're not going to take
anyone back.

175
00:11:08,233 --> 00:11:09,233
Just stay here, son.

176
00:11:09,367 --> 00:11:10,567
You might get hurt.

177
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:12,433
They are armed.

178
00:11:26,567 --> 00:11:27,033
Hey!

179
00:11:27,467 --> 00:11:28,567
Red, Red, Red.

180
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:30,567
- Calm down. Calm down!
- I need to get Yenyen back.

181
00:11:30,700 --> 00:11:32,467
I won't let her mother have her.

182
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:33,467
Mom, I have to do something!

183
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:35,533
Okay, okay! Sit down.

184
00:11:35,667 --> 00:11:37,233
Sit down, son. Calm down, okay?

185
00:11:37,367 --> 00:11:38,733
Calm down.

186
00:11:40,533 --> 00:11:45,133
We need to plan this carefully.

187
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:50,567
Amanda's confident
because she has Lucho.

188
00:11:50,700 --> 00:11:52,700
We can't be impulsive.

189
00:11:52,833 --> 00:11:54,433
I don't trust Lucho.

190
00:11:54,567 --> 00:11:56,567
He might do something to us.

191
00:11:56,700 --> 00:11:59,567
Victor, please. Stop whatever
business you're planning to do

192
00:11:59,700 --> 00:12:02,200
with that man.

193
00:12:02,333 --> 00:12:04,700
Now you know his true colors.

194
00:12:04,833 --> 00:12:06,800
He's evil too.

195
00:12:08,067 --> 00:12:12,633
Take back the money you invested
in that business.

196
00:12:12,767 --> 00:12:15,133
And then stay away from him.

197
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:20,267
I don't want you to be
associated with him anymore.

198
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:24,400
I don't want you to get involved
with his illegal dealings.

199
00:12:49,667 --> 00:12:51,133
This will be your room.

200
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:55,700
I know you're upset with me.

201
00:12:55,833 --> 00:12:59,633
But it's better than you staying
with those demons.

202
00:12:59,767 --> 00:13:02,300
You got me back, Mom.

203
00:13:02,433 --> 00:13:05,733
Let's not talk about that.

204
00:13:05,867 --> 00:13:08,200
Let's leave the decision
to the court

205
00:13:08,333 --> 00:13:12,200
regarding your accusations
against Mama Rina.

206
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:16,900
They couldn't prove their
accusations against me.

207
00:13:17,033 --> 00:13:20,967
But I still went to jail
because of their influence.

208
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:23,633
But this is different, Eden.

209
00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:25,633
Rina really is guilty.

210
00:13:27,467 --> 00:13:28,700
I love Red.

211
00:13:30,867 --> 00:13:32,700
And I love his family.

212
00:13:33,933 --> 00:13:36,567
They're not perfect, Mom.

213
00:13:36,700 --> 00:13:40,267
But I know they love me too.

214
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:41,833
They ruined us.

215
00:13:41,967 --> 00:13:44,500
Can't you still see it?

216
00:13:44,633 --> 00:13:48,767
They should have advised you
to reconcile with me

217
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:50,733
if they love you.

218
00:13:50,867 --> 00:13:53,067
Because I'm your mother.

219
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:54,633
But no.

220
00:13:57,833 --> 00:14:00,067
They keep you away from me.

221
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:02,267
You know why?

222
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:07,400
Because they want to use you
to take revenge on me.

223
00:14:07,533 --> 00:14:11,933
They will let you marry Red
to get you.

224
00:14:12,067 --> 00:14:14,267
To have a right to you.

225
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:17,667
Red and I love each other, Mom!

226
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:21,067
Red has been wanting
to marry me.

227
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:23,833
Can't you hear me?

228
00:14:23,967 --> 00:14:26,800
Rina is just using you
to hurt me.

229
00:14:26,933 --> 00:14:27,800
That's not true, Mom.

230
00:14:27,967 --> 00:14:31,733
They will only ruin your life!

231
00:14:31,867 --> 00:14:32,933
That's not true.

232
00:14:33,067 --> 00:14:34,933
Rina often says that to my face.

233
00:14:35,067 --> 00:14:36,200
That's why I had to do this.

234
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:39,200
I will never let them hurt you!

235
00:14:39,333 --> 00:14:42,233
You don't want me to get hurt?

236
00:14:42,367 --> 00:14:44,833
Why did you kick me out?

237
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:46,400
I needed you at that time.

238
00:14:46,533 --> 00:14:48,867
Why did you drive me away?

239
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,533
Mom!

240
00:14:50,667 --> 00:14:52,467
Mom, I'm sorry.

241
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:53,467
Mom...

242
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:58,267
Go with your man.

243
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,467
They need you more!

244
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:05,833
It hurts.

245
00:15:07,900 --> 00:15:14,433
But I'll start getting used
to a life without you!

246
00:15:14,567 --> 00:15:15,867
I didn't drive you away.

247
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,500
You drove my child and me away!

248
00:15:17,633 --> 00:15:19,533
I can never do that because
I love you so much!

249
00:15:19,667 --> 00:15:23,067
I didn't abandon you!

250
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:25,400
I waited for so long.

251
00:15:25,533 --> 00:15:28,233
Days, months.

252
00:15:28,367 --> 00:15:30,833
But you didn't show up.

253
00:15:30,967 --> 00:15:33,000
Why didn't you show up, Mom?

254
00:15:33,133 --> 00:15:36,267
Because I need to get ready.

255
00:15:36,433 --> 00:15:39,933
I need to fight Rina's evilness.

256
00:15:45,900 --> 00:15:49,467
You have no idea what they did
to me, right?

257
00:15:55,700 --> 00:15:58,833
You have no idea what
they did to me, right?

258
00:16:02,300 --> 00:16:03,467
They're monsters.

259
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:07,500
They are worse than the devil!

260
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:16,633
Are you hungry? Here, eat this!

261
00:16:16,767 --> 00:16:19,433
So now tell me.

262
00:16:19,567 --> 00:16:23,867
How does it feel to get rejected
by your own child?

263
00:16:25,033 --> 00:16:30,633
How does it feel to be disowned
by your own flesh and blood?

264
00:16:30,767 --> 00:16:32,567
Why?

265
00:16:32,700 --> 00:16:34,300
Why?

266
00:16:34,433 --> 00:16:37,233
Are you really asking why?

267
00:16:37,367 --> 00:16:39,367
Look at yourself, Amanda!

268
00:16:39,500 --> 00:16:41,667
What kind of a human are you?
You're a worthless mother!

269
00:16:41,833 --> 00:16:43,900
You're a worthless person!

270
00:16:54,867 --> 00:16:57,600
Now tell me.

271
00:16:57,733 --> 00:17:02,733
Should you love that family?

272
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:08,033
Are you going to choose them
over me?

273
00:17:08,167 --> 00:17:11,933
Are you going to replace me with
those people who made me suffer?

274
00:17:18,067 --> 00:17:20,167
I would have been dead
if I didn't meet Lucho.

275
00:17:20,300 --> 00:17:23,733
You would have never
seen me again.

276
00:17:27,967 --> 00:17:30,300
Eden, no matter how often
you turn your back on me...

277
00:17:30,433 --> 00:17:33,100
leave me...

278
00:17:33,233 --> 00:17:35,633
I will always be here for you.

279
00:17:35,767 --> 00:17:39,800
Even if you don't listen to me,

280
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:42,667
I will still be here
as your mother.

281
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:45,267
No matter how distant
you are from me.

282
00:17:49,467 --> 00:17:52,300
I can feel all your sufferings.

283
00:17:54,367 --> 00:17:57,900
From the moment you were born,

284
00:17:58,033 --> 00:18:01,400
I've been carrying a part
of your heart.

285
00:18:23,133 --> 00:18:24,200
Mom!

286
00:18:27,567 --> 00:18:29,467
Mom, I love you so much.

287
00:18:33,733 --> 00:18:37,367
I've been wanting to be
with you again.

288
00:18:43,667 --> 00:18:44,900
Really?

289
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:51,733
I knew it.

290
00:18:53,167 --> 00:18:56,900
I knew that Rina was just
messing with me.

291
00:18:57,067 --> 00:18:58,667
Mom, sorry.

292
00:19:00,233 --> 00:19:03,667
Sorry that I wasn't there
when you needed me.

293
00:19:04,900 --> 00:19:08,000
Sorry, Mom. I had no idea about
what was happening.

294
00:19:14,367 --> 00:19:18,600
Let's forget it, okay?

295
00:19:18,733 --> 00:19:21,233
What matters is that
we're together.

296
00:19:25,300 --> 00:19:27,833
We'll make our dreams come true.

297
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:36,267
Just tell me what you want.

298
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:38,533
I will give you everything.

299
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:46,533
What matters is that
you're here.

300
00:19:46,667 --> 00:19:49,333
I will give everything as long
as you're here.

301
00:19:51,933 --> 00:19:58,467
Mom, I don't need material
things.

302
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:04,133
You didn't raise me
to be like that.

303
00:20:04,300 --> 00:20:07,067
I only want a simple life.

304
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:15,067
As long as I'm with the people
I love.

305
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:17,667
You told me you love me.

306
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:32,100
Mom, can you love the people
I love?

307
00:20:32,233 --> 00:20:39,233
If you love me, you will let me
choose the life I want.

308
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:42,733
Didn't you listen to everything
I said?

309
00:20:48,867 --> 00:20:54,867
What do I need to do for you
to forget Red and his family?

310
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:58,533
What do I need to do?

311
00:20:58,667 --> 00:21:01,467
If you didn't go there,

312
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:03,833
Red and I would have been
married by now.

313
00:21:03,967 --> 00:21:05,233
He would be your son too.

314
00:21:05,367 --> 00:21:07,933
No, no. I can't accept him.

315
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:10,333
I can't accept Red.

316
00:21:10,467 --> 00:21:14,533
I can't accept him as my son.

317
00:21:14,667 --> 00:21:15,800
He's a pest.

318
00:21:15,933 --> 00:21:19,300
He and his family bring nothing
but trouble to our family.

319
00:21:19,433 --> 00:21:23,133
Now, if you won't
change your mind,

320
00:21:23,267 --> 00:21:25,900
you won't leave this room too.

321
00:21:26,033 --> 00:21:28,067
Mom, what are you going to do?

322
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:32,567
Mom!

323
00:21:32,700 --> 00:21:34,767
Mom, open the door!

324
00:21:34,900 --> 00:21:36,833
Mom!

325
00:21:38,900 --> 00:21:41,433
Mom, open the door!

326
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:45,200
Why are you doing this?

327
00:21:45,333 --> 00:21:48,533
Mom!

328
00:21:48,667 --> 00:21:54,100
Mom, open the door!

329
00:21:54,233 --> 00:21:56,300
Why do you have to do this?

330
00:21:56,433 --> 00:21:59,433
Open the door, Mom.

331
00:21:59,567 --> 00:22:01,767
Why do you have to lock me here?

332
00:22:01,900 --> 00:22:04,033
Aunt Dindi!

333
00:22:35,433 --> 00:22:36,867
Do you already have a plan?

334
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:39,167
What plan do you have in mind?

335
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:41,200
I want to take her away
from here.

336
00:22:41,333 --> 00:22:44,600
Somewhere that Red can't reach.

337
00:22:44,733 --> 00:22:45,700
Somewhere far.

338
00:22:45,833 --> 00:22:48,100
Do you know a place
where we can bring her?

339
00:22:48,233 --> 00:22:49,567
I'm glad you got out of jail.

340
00:22:49,733 --> 00:22:50,933
I posted bail.

341
00:22:51,067 --> 00:22:54,467
But Amanda won't leave me alone.

342
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:56,367
What do you want me to do?

343
00:22:56,500 --> 00:22:57,500
I'll go there.

344
00:22:57,633 --> 00:22:58,667
You can't get in here.

345
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:00,200
Bruno might hurt you.

346
00:23:00,333 --> 00:23:01,233
I don't care about them.

347
00:23:01,367 --> 00:23:02,600
Wait for me there.

348
00:23:02,733 --> 00:23:04,833
I'm so nervous I think
I'm going to urinate.

349
00:23:04,967 --> 00:23:06,767
What's taking Red so long?
